Here is a good view of the stigmas (Orange Hairs) protruding from a seed surrounded in trichomes (little mushroom heads). The job of the Stigma is to catch pollen ( Male Plant Jizz) if no pollen is present the bract (Round pod commonly misrepresented as a calyx) will stay empty and will remain a seedless female plant, but if there is pollen present, then the female plant will become pregnant and create a seed👌 @lit.farms.pics

This is a Thank you note…

Today marks 10 Years of this IG account!

I have had the privilege of capturing over a million photos of thousands of different strains. I have been lucky enough to work with the most incredible people, artists and brands in this industry. I have driven close to a half million miles to capture images of this plant,  been all over the country and have only been able to do so, because of you🙏

I have a tremendous amount of gratitude for everyone and each piece of the puzzle that has been instrumental in my success. To everyone that sticks around to comment, share and like my photos, Thank you! I’m going to keep grinding even when they are taking us down, when others are too paranoid to post, I’ll always kick out the jams 🤙

To the brands and breeders that have allowed me to impart my vision into theirs and highlight the best parts of this plant🙏 I know you’ve worked hard to get to where you are and it’s a constant struggle, so I gotta thank you. I have been able to burn the best stuff on this planet 100% because of you, and I gotta give props and thanks. You know who you are! 👊 

I got mad love for this community and how we continue to push boundaries despite the struggles we face to legitimize this industry in the public eye, and on these platforms. This Sh*t isn’t easy! I know! So again, massive thank you to all for the part you play🙏

Here’s to another 10 years💨 ~Chewy

To all my space nerds. I want you to swipe left and watch all these videos that I raised exposure and shadows… tell me what you see?  These are the only “real” photos I can find claimed by them that were taken from moon and outside space. all others are renditions and compositions, meaning not one single frame image has been provided. All those space missions, all the the landings but nobody pulled out a camera and took photos? Call me crazy if you’d like but there’s the evidence in front of you. You can do this experiment too. And before you say it’s compressed and on the internet blah blah! Why can I take virtual any other real image compressed and come up with zero of these “artifacts” left behind in the image? Enjoy your Sunday 😂

Someone asked if I could do this with my photos and I said sure… watch the video.. This is typical compression. Spread out through the image and a gradient fade from the subject. There isn’t an unnatural border around the subject. Yes compression artifacts are real, but the images that I posted before you can tell the image was added into the frame and has micro cluster pixels almost in a line around the subject…

Now I want you to watch both of these videos swipe left… where I take the image remove it and add a black background. Looks a little similar to NASA’s photos doesn’t it? And you see how the black doesn’t have compression because it’s a solid color? look at NASA’s photo if you look at the black in it it’s a solid color there’s no compression either hmmmm 🤔
